page.title: 04A Summer walk cont.
page.content: We saw both hares and rabbits on our walk, and evidence of deer,fox and pheasant tracks in the mud at the edge of a stream we crossed. The area is well-wooded and we saw elm trees which had been chopped down because they were diseased.Near to them young elms were sprouting up from underground suckers.One of the woods we passed through contained larch trees and here there was no undergrowth because of the thick carpet of pine needles. In addition to the large oak and ash trees we saw silver birch, elders and hazels.
